{
    "publish_date": "2012-09-26T15:04:06.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT8M48S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "(Circus music)", 
            "dur": "2.397", 
            "start": "15.012"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Ted N&#39; Ed&#39;s Carnival]", 
            "dur": "2.801", 
            "start": "21.725"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[John Lloyd&#39;s Inventory of the Invisible]", 
            "dur": "3.925", 
            "start": "24.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Adapted from a TEDTalk\ngiven by John Lloyd in 2009]", 
            "dur": "2.454", 
            "start": "39.124"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "June Cohen: Our next speaker\nhas spent his whole career", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "41.602"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "eliciting that sense of wonder.", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "44.266"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Please welcome John Lloyd.", 
            "dur": "1.352", 
            "start": "45.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Applause)", 
            "dur": "1.076", 
            "start": "47.166"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[Hall of Mirrors]", 
            "dur": "1.156", 
            "start": "48.266"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The question is, &quot;What is invisible?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "50.871"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s more of it\nthan you think, actually.", 
            "dur": "2.429", 
            "start": "53.225"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Everything, I would say --\neverything that matters --", 
            "dur": "2.711", 
            "start": "55.678"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Except every thing, and except matter.", 
            "dur": "4.207", 
            "start": "58.413"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We can see matter", 
            "dur": "1.422", 
            "start": "62.644"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but we can&#39;t see what&#39;s the matter.", 
            "dur": "2.628", 
            "start": "64.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We can see the stars and the planets\nbut we can&#39;t see what holds them apart,", 
            "dur": "5.108", 
            "start": "66.742"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or what draws them together.", 
            "dur": "1.374", 
            "start": "71.874"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "With matter as with people,\nwe see only the skin of things,", 
            "dur": "2.81", 
            "start": "74.191"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we can&#39;t see into the engine room,\nwe can&#39;t see what makes people tick,", 
            "dur": "3.781", 
            "start": "77.025"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at least not without difficulty,", 
            "dur": "1.524", 
            "start": "80.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the closer we look at anything,\nthe more it disappears.", 
            "dur": "3.62", 
            "start": "82.378"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, if you look\nreally closely at stuff,", 
            "dur": "2.201", 
            "start": "86.022"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if you look at the basic\nsubstructure of matter,", 
            "dur": "2.343", 
            "start": "88.247"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there isn&#39;t anything there.", 
            "dur": "1.412", 
            "start": "90.614"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Electrons disappear in a kind of fuzz,\nand there is only energy.", 
            "dur": "3.146", 
            "start": "92.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One of the interesting things\nabout invisibility is,", 
            "dur": "2.504", 
            "start": "95.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the things that we can&#39;s see,\nwe also can&#39;t understand.", 
            "dur": "2.922", 
            "start": "97.748"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Gravity is one thing that we can&#39;t see,\nand which we don&#39;t understand.", 
            "dur": "4.15", 
            "start": "100.694"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s the least understood\nof all the four fundamental forces,", 
            "dur": "2.905", 
            "start": "104.868"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the weakest, and nobody really\nknows what it is or why it&#39;s there.", 
            "dur": "3.543", 
            "start": "107.797"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For what it&#39;s worth, Sir Isaac Newton,\nthe greatest scientist who ever lived,", 
            "dur": "3.667", 
            "start": "111.364"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he thought Jesus came\nto Earth specifically", 
            "dur": "2.438", 
            "start": "115.055"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to operate the levers of gravity.", 
            "dur": "1.858", 
            "start": "117.517"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s what he thought he was there for.", 
            "dur": "1.905", 
            "start": "119.399"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, bright guy, could be wrong\non that one, I don&#39;t know.", 
            "dur": "2.723", 
            "start": "121.328"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.014", 
            "start": "124.075"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Consciousness. I see all your faces;\nI&#39;ve no idea what any of you are thinking.", 
            "dur": "4.645", 
            "start": "125.113"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Isn&#39;t that amazing?", 
            "dur": "1.068", 
            "start": "129.782"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Isn&#39;t it incredible that we can&#39;t read\neach other&#39;s minds,", 
            "dur": "2.762", 
            "start": "130.874"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when we can touch each other,\ntaste each other,", 
            "dur": "2.392", 
            "start": "133.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "perhaps, if we get close enough,\nbut we can&#39;t read each other&#39;s minds.", 
            "dur": "3.334", 
            "start": "136.076"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I find that quite astonishing.", 
            "dur": "1.51", 
            "start": "139.434"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the Sufi faith,\nthis great Middle Eastern religion", 
            "dur": "2.94", 
            "start": "140.968"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which some claim\nis the root of all religions,", 
            "dur": "2.309", 
            "start": "143.932"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Sufi masters are\nall telepaths, so they say,", 
            "dur": "4.756", 
            "start": "146.265"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but their main exercise of telepathy", 
            "dur": "2.503", 
            "start": "151.045"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is to send out powerful signals\nto the rest of us that it doesn&#39;t exist.", 
            "dur": "4.102", 
            "start": "153.572"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that&#39;s why we don&#39;t think it exists;\nthe Sufi masters working on us.", 
            "dur": "3.334", 
            "start": "157.698"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the question of consciousness\nand artificial intelligence,", 
            "dur": "3.399", 
            "start": "161.818"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "artificial intelligence has really,\nlike the study of consciousness,", 
            "dur": "3.221", 
            "start": "165.241"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gotten nowhere, we have no idea\nhow consciousness works.", 
            "dur": "2.629", 
            "start": "168.486"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Not only have they not created\nartificial intelligence,", 
            "dur": "2.625", 
            "start": "171.139"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they haven&#39;t yet created\nartificial stupidity.", 
            "dur": "2.405", 
            "start": "173.788"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.752", 
            "start": "176.217"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The laws of physics: invisible,\neternal, omnipresent, all powerful.", 
            "dur": "4.092", 
            "start": "177.993"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Remind you of anyone?", 
            "dur": "1.142", 
            "start": "182.109"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Interesting.", 
            "dur": "1.344", 
            "start": "184.052"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m, as you can guess,\nnot a materialist, I&#39;m an immaterialist.", 
            "dur": "3.166", 
            "start": "185.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;ve found a very useful\nnew word -- ignostic.", 
            "dur": "2.748", 
            "start": "188.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Okay? I&#39;m an ignostic.", 
            "dur": "1.258", 
            "start": "191.382"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "[God?]", 
            "dur": "1.057", 
            "start": "192.664"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I refuse to be drawn on the question\non whether God exists", 
            "dur": "2.715", 
            "start": "193.745"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "until somebody properly defines the terms.", 
            "dur": "2.124", 
            "start": "196.484"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Another thing we can&#39;t see\nis the human genome.", 
            "dur": "2.625", 
            "start": "198.632"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this is increasingly peculiar,\nbecause about 20 years ago", 
            "dur": "4.994", 
            "start": "201.281"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when they started delving into the genome,\nthey thought it would probably contain", 
            "dur": "3.858", 
            "start": "206.299"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "around 100 thousand genes.", 
            "dur": "1.308", 
            "start": "210.181"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Every year since,\nit&#39;s been revised downwards.", 
            "dur": "3.361", 
            "start": "211.513"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We now think there are likely\nto be just over 20 thousand genes", 
            "dur": "3.393", 
            "start": "214.898"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the human genome.", 
            "dur": "1.216", 
            "start": "218.315"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is extraordinary,\nbecause rice -- get this --", 
            "dur": "3.254", 
            "start": "219.555"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "rice is known to have 38 thousand genes.", 
            "dur": "2.942", 
            "start": "222.833"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Potatoes have 48 chromosomes,\ntwo more than people,", 
            "dur": "5.001", 
            "start": "225.799"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the same as a gorilla.", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "230.824"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.47", 
            "start": "232.408"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can&#39;t see these things,\nbut they are very strange.", 
            "dur": "2.976", 
            "start": "235.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The stars by day, I always\nthink that&#39;s fascinating.", 
            "dur": "2.693", 
            "start": "238.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The universe disappears.", 
            "dur": "1.305", 
            "start": "241.082"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The more light there is,\nthe less you can see.", 
            "dur": "2.276", 
            "start": "242.411"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Time. Nobody can see time.", 
            "dur": "2.369", 
            "start": "245.811"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I don&#39;t know if you know this.", 
            "dur": "1.469", 
            "start": "248.204"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There&#39;s a big movement in modern physics", 
            "dur": "2.727", 
            "start": "249.697"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to decide that time doesn&#39;t really exist,", 
            "dur": "2.01", 
            "start": "252.448"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because it&#39;s too inconvenient\nfor the figures.", 
            "dur": "2.307", 
            "start": "254.482"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s much easier if it&#39;s not really there.", 
            "dur": "2.026", 
            "start": "256.813"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can&#39;t see the future, obviously,", 
            "dur": "2.36", 
            "start": "258.863"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you can&#39;t see the past,\nexcept in your memory.", 
            "dur": "2.696", 
            "start": "261.247"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One of the interesting\nthings about the past", 
            "dur": "2.063", 
            "start": "263.967"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is you particularly can&#39;t see --", 
            "dur": "1.619", 
            "start": "266.054"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "my son asked me this the other day,", 
            "dur": "1.676", 
            "start": "267.697"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Dad, can you remember\nwhat I was like when I was two?", 
            "dur": "2.539", 
            "start": "269.397"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I said, &quot;Yes.&quot; He said, &quot;Why can&#39;t I?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.008", 
            "start": "271.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Isn&#39;t that extraordinary?", 
            "dur": "1.192", 
            "start": "273.992"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You cannot remember what happened to you\nearlier than the age of two or three.", 
            "dur": "4.086", 
            "start": "275.208"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which is great news for psychoanalysts,\nbecause otherwise they&#39;d be out of a job.", 
            "dur": "3.841", 
            "start": "279.318"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because that&#39;s where all the stuff happens", 
            "dur": "2.412", 
            "start": "283.183"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "2.445", 
            "start": "285.619"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that makes you who you are.", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "288.088"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Another thing you can&#39;t see\nis the grid on which we hang.", 
            "dur": "2.786", 
            "start": "291.359"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is fascinating.", 
            "dur": "1.023", 
            "start": "294.169"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You probably know, some of you,\nthat cells are continually renewed.", 
            "dur": "3.473", 
            "start": "295.216"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Skin flakes off, hairs grow,\nnails, that kind of stuff --", 
            "dur": "3.178", 
            "start": "298.713"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but every cell in your body\nis replaced at some point.", 
            "dur": "3.109", 
            "start": "301.915"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Taste buds, every ten days or so.", 
            "dur": "2.443", 
            "start": "305.048"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Livers and internal organs\ntake a bit longer.", 
            "dur": "2.743", 
            "start": "307.515"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Spine takes several years.", 
            "dur": "1.626", 
            "start": "310.282"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But at the end of seven years,\nnot one cell in your body", 
            "dur": "3.531", 
            "start": "311.932"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "remains from what was there\nseven years ago.", 
            "dur": "2.788", 
            "start": "315.487"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The question is:\nwho then are we? What are we?", 
            "dur": "2.789", 
            "start": "318.299"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What is this thing that we hang on?", 
            "dur": "2.011", 
            "start": "321.112"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That is actually us?", 
            "dur": "1.533", 
            "start": "323.147"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Atoms, can&#39;t see them. Nobody ever will.", 
            "dur": "3.108", 
            "start": "324.704"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They&#39;re smaller\nthan the wavelength of light.", 
            "dur": "2.137", 
            "start": "327.836"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Gas, can&#39;t see that.", 
            "dur": "1.271", 
            "start": "329.997"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Interesting, somebody\nmentioned 1600 recently.", 
            "dur": "2.341", 
            "start": "331.292"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Gas was invented in 1600\nby a Dutch chemist called van Helmont.", 
            "dur": "3.777", 
            "start": "333.657"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s said to be the most successful ever\ninvention of a word by a known individual.", 
            "dur": "5.377", 
            "start": "338.448"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Quite good. He also invented a word\ncalled &quot;blas,&quot; meaning astral radiation.", 
            "dur": "5.491", 
            "start": "343.849"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Didn&#39;t catch on, unfortunately.", 
            "dur": "1.889", 
            "start": "349.364"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.001", 
            "start": "351.277"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But well done, him.", 
            "dur": "1.071", 
            "start": "352.302"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Light -- you can&#39;t see light.", 
            "dur": "2.201", 
            "start": "353.397"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When it&#39;s dark, in a vacuum,", 
            "dur": "1.414", 
            "start": "355.622"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "if a person shines a beam of light", 
            "dur": "2.165", 
            "start": "357.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "straight across your eyes,\nyou won&#39;t see it.", 
            "dur": "2.231", 
            "start": "359.249"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Slightly technical, some physicists\nwill disagree with this.", 
            "dur": "2.844", 
            "start": "361.504"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But it&#39;s odd that you can&#39;t see\nthe beam of light,", 
            "dur": "2.341", 
            "start": "364.372"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you can only see what it hits.", 
            "dur": "1.485", 
            "start": "366.737"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Electricity, can&#39;t see that.", 
            "dur": "1.357", 
            "start": "368.246"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Don&#39;t let anyone tell you\nthey understand electricity, they don&#39;t.", 
            "dur": "3.144", 
            "start": "369.627"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Nobody knows what it is.", 
            "dur": "1.162", 
            "start": "372.795"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.007", 
            "start": "373.981"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You probably think the electrons\nin an electric wire move instantaneously", 
            "dur": "3.508", 
            "start": "375.012"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "down a wire, don&#39;t you,\nat the speed of light,", 
            "dur": "2.39", 
            "start": "378.544"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when you turn the light on, they don&#39;t.", 
            "dur": "2.072", 
            "start": "380.958"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Electrons bumble down the wire,", 
            "dur": "1.643", 
            "start": "383.054"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about the speed of spreading\nhoney, they say.", 
            "dur": "2.388", 
            "start": "384.721"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Galaxies -- hundred billion of them,", 
            "dur": "1.735", 
            "start": "387.133"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "estimated in the universe.\nHundred billion.", 
            "dur": "2.082", 
            "start": "388.892"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How many can we see?", 
            "dur": "1.347", 
            "start": "390.998"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Five. Five, out of a hundred billion\ngalaxies, with the naked eye.", 
            "dur": "3.672", 
            "start": "392.369"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And one of them is quite difficult to see,\nunless you&#39;ve got very good eyesight.", 
            "dur": "3.763", 
            "start": "396.065"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Radio waves. There&#39;s another thing.", 
            "dur": "1.689", 
            "start": "399.852"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Heinrich Hertz, when he discovered\nradio waves, in 1887,", 
            "dur": "3.187", 
            "start": "401.565"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he called them radio waves\nbecause they radiated.", 
            "dur": "2.382", 
            "start": "404.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Somebody said to him,\n&quot;What&#39;s the point of these, Heinrich?", 
            "dur": "2.835", 
            "start": "407.182"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What&#39;s the point of these radio waves\nthat you&#39;ve found?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.709", 
            "start": "410.041"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And he said, &quot;Well, I&#39;ve no idea,", 
            "dur": "1.595", 
            "start": "412.774"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but I guess somebody will find\na use for them someday.", 
            "dur": "2.583", 
            "start": "414.393"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The biggest thing that&#39;s invisible\nto us is what we don&#39;t know.", 
            "dur": "3.037", 
            "start": "417"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It is incredible how little we know.", 
            "dur": "2.913", 
            "start": "420.061"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thomas Edison once said,", 
            "dur": "1.299", 
            "start": "422.998"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;We don&#39;t know one percent\nof one millionth about anything.&quot;", 
            "dur": "4.603", 
            "start": "424.321"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;ve come to the conclusion --", 
            "dur": "3.142", 
            "start": "428.948"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because you ask this other question:\n&quot;What&#39;s another thing we can&#39;t see?&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.47", 
            "start": "432.114"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The point, most of us. What&#39;s the point?", 
            "dur": "1.949", 
            "start": "435.608"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The point -- what I&#39;ve got it down to", 
            "dur": "1.762", 
            "start": "437.581"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is there are only two questions\nreally worth asking.", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "439.367"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "&quot;Why are we here?&quot;,", 
            "dur": "1.012", 
            "start": "441.891"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and &quot;What should\nwe do about it while we are?&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.521", 
            "start": "442.927"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To help you, I&#39;ve got two things to leave\nyou with, from two great philosophers,", 
            "dur": "4.037", 
            "start": "445.472"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "perhaps two of the greatest philosopher\nthinkers of the 20th century.", 
            "dur": "3.286", 
            "start": "449.533"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One a mathematician and engineer,\nand the other a poet.", 
            "dur": "2.766", 
            "start": "452.843"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The first is Ludwig Wittgenstein,", 
            "dur": "2.79", 
            "start": "455.633"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who said, &quot;I don&#39;t know why we are here,", 
            "dur": "2.782", 
            "start": "458.447"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but I am pretty sure it&#39;s not\nin order to enjoy ourselves.&quot;", 
            "dur": "2.856", 
            "start": "461.253"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.032", 
            "start": "464.133"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "He was a cheerful bastard, wasn&#39;t he?", 
            "dur": "1.903", 
            "start": "465.189"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.166", 
            "start": "467.116"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And secondly, and lastly,\nW.H. Auden, one of my favorite poets,", 
            "dur": "5.498", 
            "start": "468.306"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "who said, &quot;We are here\non Earth to help others.", 
            "dur": "4.611", 
            "start": "473.828"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What the others\nare here for, I&#39;ve no idea.&quot;", 
            "dur": "3.394", 
            "start": "478.463"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Laughter)", 
            "dur": "1.519", 
            "start": "481.881"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "(Applause)", 
            "dur": "2.655", 
            "start": "483.424"
        }, 
